This sword is an interesting case. Without the combo of Relentless Strikes + Whirlwind Blade to allow it to stack up against other swords for boss damage, you have to get creative. Relentless + En Guard can give some good quick burst of damage, while Thresh + Assassins Blade could have its place against Taniks as Div. PvP: It really doesnt matter.

Opening Shot is arguably the best in slot perk. Rangefinder is generally the go to (it does add ~3M of base range) but Hawkmoon is a run and gun weapon (in my opinion) - if you want range, run a 120 or Luna Faction boots. Opening Shot gives a serious bonus to accuracy on ground and in air and helps guarantee landing the first crit (or 7 stack OHKO if you wait for perk to reset). Moving Target is nearly worthless due to high base AA stat.

The medium zoom scopes add +3 / 4 to zoom which has a massive impact on damage drop off. Model 8 Red pushes it to 17 zoom which makes this the best in slot SMG by a long shot (get it? Because it has more range?) pushing a 60 stat SMG to 20M base range.

The medium zoom scopes add +3 / 4 to zoom which has a massive impact on damage drop off. Model 8 Red pushes it to 17 zoom which makes this the best in slot SMG by a long shot (get it? Because it has more range?) pushing a 60 stat SMG to 20M base range. Deciding between Kill Clip and Iron Reach comes down to deciding what you want your smg to be. Iron Reach gives it an extra 3m of range (and with smgs, every metre counts) making it a better dueling weapon, while Kill Clips damage buff gives it a nutty ttk and an excellent snowball machine.

Frenzy is +50 to reload, so that perk alone puts Fatebringer at max reload speed. Loader will still add a scalar so it will be faster. Kill Clip does not boost Explosive Payload damage, just the impact damage. Explosive sometimes interferes with Firefly explosions.

Kill Clip does not improve TTK - just forgiveness and effective range. Opening Shot is still likely the best in slot, but do not sleep on Eye of the Storm for a mid-duel consistency boost, because of its mid-combat proc condition often occuring during 1v1 duels, the accuracy bump EotS grants could be excellent for finishing a fight.

Choosing between Reservoir Burst and HIR in PvE depends on the situation. HIR for boss damage and Reservoir Burst for general use and add clear. HIR is the clear winner for PvP, since it reduces the bolts needed for a kill while procced, and one stack of Heating Up makes the recoil perfectly vertical for easier bolt control.

However this allows it to reach into more interesting builds while not focusing wholly on range. If you prefer the feel of Eyasluna then a Rangefinder + Moving Target roll is the play for the range, but Unrelenting is a surprisingly good 6s perk, while Demo can be used to better use your now slower charging grenades.

The God Combo of Quickdraw + Snapshot returns on a 90 rpm sniper. Personally Id go all in on Handling with a Qd + Snap sniper, to help with the stow speed and attempt to match the old version of Quickdraw as closely as possible (potentially even using Quick Access Sling if you can justify the loss of the option of air shots. Despite the return of the old combo, dont discount Firmly Planted as an excellent accuracy booster when crouching.
